#### SCRAPE

scrape_amazon <- function(page_num) {
  url_reviews <- paste0("https://www.amazon.com/Google-GA00439-US-Chromecast-3rd-Generation/product-reviews/B015UKRNGS/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_viewopt_srt?ie=UTF8&reviewerType=avp_only_reviews&pageNumber=", page_num)
  doc <- read_html(url_reviews)

  map_dfr(doc %>% html_elements("[id^='customer_review']"), ~ data.frame(
    review_title = .x %>% html_element(".review-title") %>% html_text2(),
    review_text = .x %>% html_element(".review-text-content") %>% html_text2(),
    review_star = .x %>% html_element(".review-rating") %>% html_text2(),
    date = .x %>% html_element(".review-date") %>% html_text2() %>% gsub(".*vom ", "", .),
    author = .x %>% html_element(".a-profile-name") %>% html_text2(),
    page = page_num
  )) %>%
    as_tibble %>%
    return()
}

# extract testing
df <- scrape_amazon(page_num = 20)

df_total <- data.frame()
for (x in 1:1000){
  each_page <- scrape_amazon(page_num = x)
  df <- data.frame(each_page)
  df_total <- rbind(df_total, df)
}
# export to csv 
write.csv(df_total, "google_chromecast.csv", row.names = TRUE)
